deck_excerpt: Currently the most viable way to summon Magia Master in Masterduel! Through Dogmatika!
deck_description:
Dragon Master Magia's absurd summoning materials mean that this Dragoon wannabe can only be properly summoned through Dogmatika as they mill Extra Deck monsters to the GY and search for ritual monsters. It may be a bit difficult and gimmicky to bring this guy out, but the payoff is incredible, with Dragon Master Magia's TRIPLE negate/destroy, and it floats into Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon for free! While not the most competitively viable option, it certainly is cool!

Otherwise, this deck functions as a regular Dogmatika deck. If you want a thorough guide to play Dogmatika, check out my article from last year.

Here is the combo to bring out Dragon Master Magia through Dogmatika:

Nadir Servant + Iblee + Ultimate Fusion = Mill most of your opponent's Extra Deck (2-4 left in opponent's Extra), Alba Zoa (4K beatstick and towers), Magia Master (monster negate, spell negate, trap negate), Fleurdelis (monster negate handtrap), Secure Gardna (battle dmg protection) and +1-3 card draws.
  1. Normal summon Iblee. 
  2. Link summon Almiraj using Iblee. Iblee's trigger effect will summon her to your opponent's side of the field (turning on the "Iblee Lock"). 
  3. Link away Almiraj to summon Secure Gardna. 
  4. Activate Nadir Servant sending Garura to the GY searching Ecclesia from deck. Garura draws you 1 card.
  5. Special summon Ecclesia. Ecclesia searches for Dogmatikamatrix. (If you already have Matrix, search Dogmatika Punishment instead). 
  6. Activate Dogmatikamatrix, searching first for Alba Zoa, then Maximus.
  7. Special summon Maximus by banishing Almiraj from the GY. 
  8. Activate Maximus' effect, sending Herald of the Arc Light and Titaniklad (while also milling two of your opponent's Extra Deck).
  9. Herald of the Arc Light searches for Dogmatikalamity. 
  10. Activate Dogmatikalamity to ritual summon Alba Zoa by sending to GY Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon from the Extra Deck. 
  11. Activate Alba Zoa to mill/handrip your opponent's hand/Extra Deck. 
  12. Activate Dogmatikamatrix to send another Herald of the Arc Light to the GY.
  13. Herald of the Arc Light searches for Illusion of Chaos from the Deck.
  14. Activate Illusion of Chao's effect to search for Magician's Souls and place it on top of the deck.
  15. Activate Magician's Souls effect to send from Deck to GY Illusion of Chaos and summon itself from hand. Bonus: Send to GY 1-2 spells with Magician Souls and draw cards.
  16. Set on your field any spell of traps, including Ultimate Fusion.
  17. At the End Phase, activate Titaniklad's effect to add to hand Fleurdelis. 
  18. During your opponent's Main Phase, activate Ultimate Fusion shuffling back Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon + Illusion of Chaos to fusion summon Dragon Magia Master.

GLHF Duelists!

deck_excerpt: Raidraptors for Master Duel Post Selection Pack: Wings of the Guardian
deck_description: Raidraptors for Master Duel Post Selection Pack: Wings of the Guardian

The Deck is pretty straightforward so I'll just go over the weird techs and ratios:

- Three Big Winged Berformet for the grind. The standard combo already requires two, and without Fiendsmith you have no way to recycle them outside of Lubellion cope. Side one out going second.

- One Nightmare Apprentice (because it is expensive) because it's a dead body in Branded Fusion lines. It's usually used as an additional Gazelle target when you don't have Branded Fusion access, gets more value out of King Berfomet if you already dumped Diabellze and Tao, and is also a Big Wing target for follow up. Going second it helps you set up Knightmare Phoenix more easily.

- Springans Kitt is to prevent the Branded Fusion Line from being wasteful as you can't resolve the Illusion search effect of Gazelle twice, and also helps get garnets like Tao or Big Wing back into the Deck. The handfixing also limits hand knowledge to some extent.

- You already lose a lot of advantage using handtraps so I chose to run Book of Eclipse over something like Droplet. It actually does something going first (protects Gazelle or an Albaz Fusion from Imperm/Veiler). There is potential value as a Nib counter but you have such great follow up anyways.

- Veidos the Eruption Dragon of Extinction is mainly for Snake-Eye and Yubel, however quick Field Spell removal in general is extremely handy. It also shuts down specifically Kashtira which is always welcome.

 

Prioritize your grind unless you are confident you can go for letal that turn. Resource management is a must--we have great grind but it's not Virtual World crazy. Branded Fusion as follow up is really strong in this Deck as it guarantees Lubellion access which can make an Illusion Beast in a pinch.

deck_excerpt: Something toadally special. Play a slow control trap deck that does decently well in modern yugioh.
deck_description:
Post Info, Magicolloidal Sol makes the frogs a compelling engine again in Moden Paleo.This is the build I have settle on after a bit of tweaking. I was a morganite hater, but it makes grindin with the deck so much easier, and you can actually use the 2nd normal if swap frog eats a veiler or imperm. 

Balance of Judgment is insane since decks likes to clog up their backrows with random stuff. I was hater until I realized Waboku/Rise is just a turnskip.

I was a big desire fan for a while, since Leanchoilia is mini Marella at that point, but you go -9 with it.(Its decent, but I don't really like managing my facedown banish for traptrick/marella plays. 

Extra Deck is kinda tight, but I like 2nd Ty-Ph instead of Downerd because it is a floodgate (you usually lose the first one trying to break the board). Honestly might cut SP or Gigantic Spright.

2 Toad is great for flexbility, and you can totally make 2.

No 2 is just great card for ending game.

This pack will update us with new decks and support cards. Today we will test to see what decks will change in the upcoming version. deck_excerpt: Just because this deck doesn't have main deck handtraps does not mean it can't win.

mazzo basato sul utilizzare i mostri joker/arcana knight per mettere creature sul campo per tributarli alle bestie divine e ogni tanto usare anche quelle del oppo e anche searchare il buon caro slifer avendo piu o meno sempre carte in mano per pomparlo di atk.

Nonostante le mani brick che si possono avere (che purtroppo con questo tipo di mazzo succede spesso) il mazzo ha un game plan ben preciso in mente.

Spieghero ogni carta e scopo della loro aggiunta nel modo migliore che posso

Jack, Queen e Jack's knight: l'engine che fa girare il mazzo necessita di questi gialloni purtroppo. 2 coppie di ognuno per non correre il rischio di pescarli tutti insieme alle varie carte che aggiungono oppure evocano queste carte cosa molto probabile. 

Slifer, Ra e Obelisk: I pay-off. Se non sono gia in mano, che il piu delle volte non e un problema, ci sono tanti modi di cercarli (thunderspeed e soul energy max) oppure di averli nel grave (foolish e revelation). Da non dimenticare gli effetti di ra e obelisk che possono rimuovere pezzi del oppo. 2x di slifer per lo stesso motivo di prima

Joker's knight: free special che ritorna nella mano per slifer e manda un potenziale nome per potenziare l'effetto di court of cards 

Joker's straight: carta che ci permette di mettere tanti pezzi sull board con un lock in questo caso non rilevante (almeno che non si voglia giocare con l'extra deck) che si aggiunge alla mano nel end phase per il buon caro slifer

Thunderspeed summon: il pezzo che unisce le bestie divine con i knight. quick che ti permette di evocare un lvl 10 durante il turno del oppo che se controlli i 3 nomi specificati sulla carta puoi praticamente aggiungere slifer e metterlo sul campo. "searchabile" con la prossima carta

Joker's wild: si usa per copiare thunderspeed summon e anche si aggiunge alla mano nell end step. 3 copie per trovarlo piu facilmente e poi ce anche trap trick per vederlo piu spesso

Court of cards: 1 solo effetto per turno la rende molto piu schifosa di quelle che e gia pero pescare o evocare non fa mai male

Millennium revelation: manda divine beast al cimitero e aggiunge monster reborn alla mano che e fondamentale per le carte che hanno bisogno delle bestie divine nell graveyard (revived sky god e the breaking ruin god) e per quelle sul campo (thunderforce attack e fist of fate)

Soul crossing: anche se non searchabile removal molto forte che purtroppo ti locka in un solo effetto non bestia divina per il resto del turno

Foolish burial e goods: al mazzo piace avere spell e monstri nell grave sia per gli effetti delle carte joker che si riaggiungono che le carte di archetipo bestia divina (breaking god, revived e soul energy). 

Trap trick: da accesso alle trappole che purtroppo non si possono searchare. L'uso piu probabile e quello di settare joker's wild pero dipende sempre. Motivo per cui si giocano almeno 2 copie delle trappole siccome devi bandire una per settare l'altra.

Soul energy max: search di obelisk e non e male se c'e gia in campo. 

The revived sky god: il grande sogno di avere 6 carte in mano con slifer sul campo.

The breaking ruin god, fist of fate e thunderforce attack: carte molto meme anche molto belle e molto forti se risolvono

Monster reborn: se ti devo spiegare questa sei un caso perso

Conclusione: non sono bravo a spiegare e sono le 4 di mattina quindi ho sonno. mazzo con tanta sinergia che puo brickare mooooooooooooolto perche e un mazzo che prova di giocare tutti i god e purtroppo l'unico con supporti buoni e ra e anche quello lo devi giocare con i horus se vuoi fare qualcosa. No extra e no handtrap significa che non potrai competere contro altri mazzi competenti che hanno spazio per quelle.
PURE Competive hero deck, good for local tournamnent.

The idea to mix True Draco with Exodia Millennium came from a strong desire to find a way to make use of the Millennium main deck monsters' main mechanic of placing themselves as Continuous Spells. Originally I experimented with a Crystal Beast engine and then Weather Painters, but once i disocvered True Dracos, I decided this was the best combinationt to give Millennium's main conceit a new strength (aside from Snake Eyes). The Extra and Side Decks are incomplete, but the Extra Deck is mostly going to be used to bring out Exodia and hope for an OTK.

The basic strategy revolves around what you top deck. If you get mostly Millennium, you search Ankh and bring out Unstoppable Exodia. Supposing you top deck only Sengenjin, you're going to be out 4000 LP, so Ghost Sister is there to offset the drain on your life and actually give Exodia some juice.  Even if you end up with 4k LP, you still have a strong body on field that can negate any spell/trap once per turn, but come your standby [hase, you burn for 1k, so be prepared to tribute him with True Draco monster using True Draco Apocalypse. At each of your End Phases, you can search one of 3 Exodia centric cards, those being Obliterate!!!, Obliterate!!! Blaze, and Exxod Fires of Rage. Depending on your position after summoning Exodia, you'll probably want to search Exodd as it'll completely wipe your opponent's board at no cost, the only limitation being it requres a Level 10 Exodia monster on the field. If you top decked True Draco Monsters and Ankh, but nothing else, a good search would be Obliterate!!!, since it's a Continuous Trap, you can bounce your opponent's main combo piece, then on your turn tribute it to summon a True Draco. Blaze is important as it'll clear out both players' back row, allowing you to remove any monsters placed by Wedju that otehrwise take up valuable space, but it'll also activate the effects of all True Draco effects that were in your back row, allowing you to pop up to 2 spell/traps and 2 monsters on your opponents field, and then buffing Exodia + 10K. This works with Forbidden Droplet as well, as any monsters treated as Continuous Spells are counted as Spells for its effect, so you can send your pieces as you please to negate up to 5 of your opponents monsters and negate their spells at the same time.

On the True Draco side of things, you can choose to tribute a Millennium Monster as a Continuous Spell to bring out your True Dracos while sparing your important Spells and Traps. Metaltron XII is a replacement for Master Peace (god rest his soul) as the big boss monster with effect immunity. How it shines where Master Peace falters is that it can make itself entirely immune to all card effect, whereas Master Peace can only make itself immune to two card types maximum, though its second effect to pop a card and it requiring two tributes is ideal to Metaltron's required 3 and Extra Deck cheat. I'm still looking for extra deck filler for Prosperity targets as well as Metaltron cheats.

If it wasn't obvious the main appeal is how Millennium is accentuated by the True Draco tech. The deck's main weakness is handtraps and non-destruction removal. It's vulnerable to negation and his little in the way of negates on its own, so you want to hit your opponent at their choke points before they gain traction. In the side is two copies of Spell Card "Soul Exchange" which is there as removal of any of your opponents monsters to get out any of your main deck monsters, but also Exodia the Legendary Defender, a funny alternate win condition just in case. But it also has purpose aside from that, allowing you to tribute your opponent's board to bring out Defender with the combined attack of all tributed monsters, opening yourself up for another OTK. Instant Fusion is there to bring out Millennium Eyes Restrict in order to snag one of your opponents monsters on your turn, but if thy don;t give you that chance, you can steal one anyway using Millennium Eyes Illusionist. Since both monsters are "Millennium" they are included in the archetpye and searchable by Sengenjin's effect, and will be sent to back row as Continuous Spells by Wedju Temple's effect, allowing you more tribute fodder for True Dracos. Relinquished Anima is exactly the same save for being a Millennium Monster. It can be brought out with a Forbidden One piece, and you can steal one of your opponent's monsters using Illusionist. Winning with Exodia aseembled isn't the goal of this dekc, but it's not impossible, hence the draw spells and Prosperity. An important thing to note is that you cannot activate Ankh with an Exodia Piece in the GY or Banished, so only send them after summoning Exodia, or if you don't plan to at all. But if you do want hose pieces back, Exxod and Obliterate!!! can bring pieces back from the GY to hand, while Exxod can even bring them back from Banishment. If you want, you can also side in Dark Factory of Renewal, which will allow you to add TWO normal monsters from your GY to the hand, so if Blaze failed you, you can get four pieces back immediately and the head back with Exxod for the win.

Aside from that there's not much else there for the strategy, It's pretty ham-fisted which is how I like to do things.

deck_excerpt: Have you ever wanted less friends?
deck_description: Use mimighouls with melffys to stall out the game. Heavy advantage in the grind as long as pinny doesn't get hit by called by. Summoning curse, archfiend, and desert locust are all pretty hefty handrips & getting those to proc helps keep your combos the tiniest bit safer. Can use staring contest to mulligan the melffys or cerberus and get wally to get things going, and Puppy can pull out cerberus to protect your field and staring contest if needed. 2nd turn and onwards you generally want to get dragon to just keep blowing up the opponent's board and trying to wedge in damage wherever you can, and make a big push once you've thoroughly exhausted your opponent.
